The paper discusses the use of physical unclonable functions (PUFs) for secure authentication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of hash functions and password management systems, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the importance of security in mobile and embedded devices, which can be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
